<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871209-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:RealAmerica Co.</HL><DD> 12/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> RACOREAL ESTATE, REITS, LAND DEVELOPMENT (REL) </IN><TEXT>   RealAmerica Co., Lexington, Ky., said it agreed to sell certain property in Albuquerque, N.M., to closely held Capital Growth Corp., a New York-based real estate investment company, for about $36.3 million in cash and notes.    RealAmerica, a real estate investment concern, said the sale of an office building and retail complex, which accounts for about 80% of the company's assets, is expected to be completed in early 1988. The company wouldn't comment on how it will use the proceeds. The sale is subject to shareholder approval and certain closing conditions, RealAmerica said.    The property is held by a joint venture in which RealAmerica Partners Ltd. I owns an 85% interest and First National Bank in Albuquerque owns the remainder. RealAmerica Co. has a 93.75% interest in RealAmerica Partners. </TEXT></DOC>